{
  "stem": "27507.11",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And, in fact, my mother was totally separated from us until the late January '45, because only after another offensive, the Russians took the remaining part of Warsaw in January '45.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And my mother then crossed over the Vistula, over the ice, I think, to the eastern part and went back to Koper's place and left a-- and left a letter for my father.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And so we found out that she's alive, and she then came to Lublin, and we all were reunited--",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Early-- early in 1945.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, normal if one can say normal after all that.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But it was relatively normal in view of what happened before.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then we moved back to Warsaw soon, a few months later in early spring, 1945.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And because my parents had no place to live, I went to the children's home, which was kept by the Jewish committee in [POLISH], not far from Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I stayed there for quite a few months until late in 1945.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then I moved again with my mother to [POLISH], and we lived there for another few years until my father managed to arrange for us a flat in Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My father worked in Warsaw and came to see us on weekends, and then we all moved back to Warsaw three years later in 1948, and lived in Warsaw until early in 1950 when we all went to Israel.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, I went to school.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yes, I went normally to school.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the remaining part of my-- those of my uncles who survived the war, there was only one uncle, in fact, who survived the war, and there were a few aunts who survived the war.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No-- from my father's side-- from my father's side nobody survived the war in Poland.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
